<h1>Real Madrid Club de Fútbol</h1>
<p><strong>Commonly referred to as:</strong> Real Madrid</p>
<p><strong>Location:</strong> Madrid, Spain</p>
<p><strong>Competition:</strong> La Liga (Top tier of Spanish football)</p>

<h2>History</h2>
<p>Founded in 1902 as Madrid Football Club, Real Madrid has worn a white home kit traditionally. The honorific title 'Real' means 'royal' in Spanish and was given by King Alfonso XIII in 1920, along with the crown added to the club crest. Since 1947, Real Madrid has played its home matches in the 85,000-capacity Santiago Bernabéu Stadium in Madrid. Unlike most European football clubs, Real Madrid's members (socios) have owned and operated the club throughout its history.</p>

<h2>Achievements</h2>
<p>Real Madrid is one of the most widely supported football clubs globally and is the most followed football club on social media. The club is estimated to be worth $6.6 billion in 2024, making it the world's most valuable football club. In 2024, Madrid became the first football club to make €1 billion ($1.1bn) in revenue.</p>

<h3>Domestic Titles</h3>
<ul>
    <li>36 La Liga titles (Record)</li>
    <li>20 Copa del Rey</li>
    <li>13 Supercopa de España</li>
    <li>Copa Eva Duarte</li>
    <li>Copa de la Liga</li>
</ul>

<h3>International Titles</h3>
<ul>
    <li>15 European Cup/UEFA Champions League titles (Record)</li>
    <li>6 UEFA Super Cups (Record)</li>
    <li>2 UEFA Cups</li>
    <li>2 Latin Cups (Joint Record)</li>
    <li>1 Iberoamerican Cup</li>
    <li>8 FIFA Club World Championships (Record)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Notable Rivals</h2>
<p>Real Madrid has long-standing rivalries, most notably the El Clásico with Barcelona and El Derbi Madrileño with Atlético Madrid.</p>

<h2>Greatest Team of All Time</h2>
<p>The club established itself as a major force in football during the 1950s and 60s with a team that included Alfredo Di Stéfano, Ferenc Puskás, Paco Gento, and Raymond Kopa, considered by many to be the greatest of all time.</p>

<h2>Galácticos Policy</h2>
<p>Real Madrid is known for its Galácticos policy, which involves signing the world's best players, such as Ronaldo, Zinedine Zidane, and David Beckham, to create a superstar team. This policy was particularly prominent during the two eras of Florentino Pérez's presidency. Recent signings include Vinícius Júnior, Rodrygo, Jude Bellingham, and Kylian Mbappé.</p>

<h2>FIFA Recognition</h2>
<p>Real Madrid was recognized as the greatest football club of the 20th century by FIFA and the best European club by IFFHS during the same period. The club also holds several records in the UEFA Champions League, including the most wins and goals scored.</p>

<h2>Current Status</h2>
<p>As of July 2024, Real Madrid is ranked 2nd in the UEFA club rankings and 1st in the rankings for the last decade (2013–2023). In June 2024, they won their 15th Champions League title, extending their record.</p> 


